label: Engineer
description: A professional member of the engineering profession expected to exhibit highest standards of honesty and integrity
text_references: As members of this profession, engineers are expected to exhibit the highest standards of honesty and integrity
Engineers, in the fulfillment of their professional duties, shall

label: Client
description: An entity that receives engineering services and to whom engineers owe duties of loyalty and confidentiality
text_references: Act for each employer or client as faithful agents or trustees
Do not disclose client/employer information without consent

label: Employer
description: An organization or entity that employs engineers and has claims to their professional loyalty
text_references: Act for each employer or client as faithful agents or trustees
Notify employer before accepting outside work

label: Public
description: The general population whose safety, health, and welfare engineers must hold paramount
text_references: Hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public
Engineers shall strive to serve the public interest

label: Public Safety
description: The protection of the general population from harm, which engineers must prioritize above all else
text_references: Hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public
dedicated to the protection of the public health, safety, and welfare

label: Honesty
description: Truthfulness and transparency in all professional communications and conduct
text_references: exhibit the highest standards of honesty and integrity
Engineers shall be guided by honesty and integrity

label: Integrity
description: Moral uprightness and adherence to ethical principles in professional practice
text_references: exhibit the highest standards of honesty and integrity
Engineers shall be guided by honesty and integrity

label: Competence
description: Professional qualification and expertise necessary to perform engineering services safely and effectively
text_references: Perform services only in areas of their competence
Accept only qualified assignments

label: Professional Behavior
description: Conduct that meets the highest standards of ethical practice and enhances the profession
text_references: perform under a standard of professional behavior that requires adherence to the highest principles of ethical conduct

label: Confidentiality
description: The obligation to protect sensitive information obtained from clients or employers
text_references: Do not disclose client/employer information without consent
Engineers shall maintain confidentiality

label: Conflict of Interest
description: Situations where personal interests may compromise professional judgment or loyalty
text_references: Disclose actual or potential conflicts of interest
Engineers shall not be influenced by conflicting interests

label: Faithful Agent
description: Acting with complete loyalty and in the best interests of clients or employers
text_references: Act for each employer or client as faithful agents or trustees

label: Engineering Documents
description: Technical documents, plans, specifications, and reports that must conform to professional standards
text_references: Approve only engineering documents conforming to standards

label: Public Statements
description: Communications to the public that must be objective, truthful, and based on competence
text_references: Issue public statements only in an objective and truthful manner
Be objective and include all pertinent facts

label: Code Violations
description: Instances where engineering codes, standards, or regulations are not followed
text_references: Report known code violations to professional or public bodies

label: Professional Development
description: Ongoing education and skill enhancement to maintain competence
text_references: Commit to ongoing professional development

label: Deceptive Acts
description: Dishonest or misleading behaviors that engineers must avoid
text_references: Avoid deceptive acts
Engineers shall avoid deceptive acts

label: Bribery
description: Offering or accepting improper payments or gifts to influence decisions
text_references: Do not offer bribes or commissions to secure contracts
Reject inducements from suppliers

label: Professional Reputation
description: The standing and credibility of engineers and the profession that must be protected
text_references: Engineers shall not harm others' professional reputation
enhance the honor, reputation, and usefulness of the profession

label: Sustainability
description: Environmental and social responsibility in engineering practice
text_references: Support sustainability

label: Registration Laws
description: Legal requirements for professional engineering licensure and practice
text_references: Follow registration laws

label: Proprietary Rights
description: Intellectual property and ownership rights of clients and employers
text_references: Respect proprietary rights of clients
Understand employer retains rights to exclusive work materials

label: Error Correction
description: The responsibility to acknowledge and remedy mistakes in professional work
text_references: Admit and correct errors

label: Public Interest
description: The collective welfare and benefit of society that engineers should serve
text_references: Engineers shall strive to serve the public interest

label: Professional Dignity
description: Maintaining the respectability and honor of the engineering profession
text_references: Uphold professional dignity
